  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Crawler Crane/Rough Terrain Crane Operator",
  "description": "<p><u>Job Description</u></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Understand and comply with site safety requirements</li>\n  <li>Operate crawler crane or rough terrain crane, on a daily basis and safely at job sites as required</li>\n  <li>Perform daily pre-operational daily maintenance and checks before commencing lifting operations- operate machinery / equipment within safe operating procedures</li>\n  <li>Inform site supervisors immediately and stop operations, if any unsafe conditions or acts are observed during machinery / equipment operations.</li>\n  <li>Past experience operating crane in marine environment will be added advantage</li>\n  <li>Own transportation desired but not necessary</li>\n</ol>\n<p><u>Requirements</u></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Valid Certificate of Registration with MOM (Crawler crane and/or Mobile Crane)</li>\n  <li>Be able to communicate with staff and others involved in the lifting operation</li>\n  <li>Have basic knowledge of the crane safety requirement and operating procedures of the crawler cranes</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience (able to work at HDB or LTA sites). Those with new license are also welcome to apply.</li>\n  <li>Valid CSOC (WSQ Apply Workplace Safety and Health In Construction Sites)</li>\n</ol>",
